âœ” Array Sum Modulo K

ğŸ” Understanding the Problem

You want the sum of the array to be divisible by k.

Let:

sum = sum(nums)
rem = sum % k


If rem == 0 â†’ answer = 0.

Else you must reduce sum using operations.

The only operation allowed:

nums[i] = nums[i] - 1   (one operation)


Each operation reduces total sum by 1.

So if sum % k = rem, then:

ğŸ‘‰ You need rem operations.

Because after doing rem decrements, the new sum becomes divisible by k.

ğŸ¯ Key Insight
âœ” Only sum matters, not individual elements

You do not need to think about which index to change.

Since every "âˆ’1" reduces total sum by 1, minimum operations needed is:

â­ rem = sum(nums) % k

Unless all elements become negative?
ğŸŸ¢ No restriction â€” elements can become any number, even negative.
So this formula always works.

ğŸ§  Final Formula
operations = sum(nums) % k


if remainder = 0 â†’ return 0
else return remainder

âœ” Example 1

nums = [3, 9, 7], k = 5
sum = 19
19 % 5 = 4
â†’ Need 4 operations

Matches output.

âœ” Example 3

nums = [3,2], k = 6
sum = 5
5 % 6 = 5
â†’ Need 5 operations

Matches output.

ğŸ§µ Concept to Study
â­ Modulo Arithmetic

Remainder handling

